          "chapter": "GOETHE; OR, THE WRITER.",
          "text": "Goethe was the philosopher of this multiplicity; hundred-handed, Argus-eyed, able and happy to cope with this rolling miscellany of facts and sciences, and by his own versatility to dispose of them with ease;",
