          "text": ". And the more brilliant, the more unusual the man, the nearer he is to the stake. ",
          "sentence": "The color of one’s creed, neckties, eyes, thoughts, manners, speech, is sure to meet somewhere in time or space with a fatal objection from a mob that hates that particular tone. And the more brilliant, the more unusual the man, the nearer he is to the stake. Stranger always rhymes with danger. ",
