          "chapter": null,
          "text": "Time and space, the colors of the seasons, the movements of muscles and minds, all these are for writers of genius ",
          "sentence": "Time and space, the colors of the seasons, the movements of muscles and minds, all these are for writers of genius (as far as we can guess and I trust we guess right) not traditional notions which may be borrowed from the circulating library of public truths but a series of unique surprises which master artists have learned to express in their own unique way. ",
          "note": null,
          "path": "epubcfi(/6/14[Section0005.xhtml]!/4/10/1,:0,:115)",
